Arrays: whenever we have something in a group and of similar type, we should think of storing it as an array


        //Variable are like boxes/jara/containers meant for holding the values
        // 10

        //1. dataType variableName = value; [when we know the exact value to store]
        int x = 10;

        //2. dataType variableName;         [when we don't know the exact value to store]
        int age;

        // variable can hold only and only one value at a time


        We use below syntax when we know the exact values that we to store
        dataType[] arrayName = {value1, value2, value3, value4.......};


        We use below syntax if we don't know the exact values that we to store, but know their count

        dataType[] arrayName = new dataType[count]


        We must use arrays only in those cases, where we are quite sure the count of values to store won't change.
